  "prompt": "What do most japanese know about Indonesia?",
  "response": "Most Japanese people have some basic knowledge about Indonesia, including:\n\n1. Geography\n- Large archipelago in Southeast Asia\n- Located near the equator\n- Predominantly Muslim country\n- Many islands (over 17,000)\n\n2. Cultural Awareness\n- Diverse ethnic groups and cultures\n- Traditional arts like batik and wayang puppet theater\n- Known for friendly and hospitable people\n\n3. Economic Relations\n- Important trading partner for Japan\n- Source of natural resources like coal, palm oil, and minerals\n- Many Japanese companies have investments in Indonesia\n\n4. Tourism\n- Bali is very popular among Japanese tourists\n- Known for beautiful beaches and landscapes\n- Attractive destination for honeymoons and vacations\n\n5. Historical Context\n- Former Dutch colonial territory\n- Experienced Japanese occupation during World War II\n- Gained independence in 1945\n\n6. Cuisine\n- Some familiarity with Indonesian foods like satay and nasi goreng\n- Regarded as spicy and flavorful\n\n7. General Facts\n- Large population (4th most populous country)\n- Capital city is Jakarta\n- Emerging economy with growing middle class\n\nHowever, individual knowledge can vary significantly depending on personal interest and exposure.",
